 Barcelona defeated Juventus on Saturday to win the Champions League for the fifth time. Goals from Ivan Rakitic, Luis Suarez and Neymar gave Barcelona a 3-1 victory over Juventus and secured the Spanish sideâ€™s fifth Champions League title on Saturday. Rakitic opened the scoring in the fourth minute. Although the Italians fought back with an Alvaro Morata equaliser after the break, Suarez got the second and Neymar made sure of victory in stoppage time. Victory gave Barcelona a momentous treble of the Champions League, Spanish title and Spanish Cup. 